article.description: — Justin Amadi had 16 points as James Madison narrowly beat Wright State 78-76 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Amadi lifts James Madison past Wright State 78-76
article.linkText: Amadi lifts James Madison past Wright State 78-76
article.story: NAPLES, Fla. -- — Justin Amadi had 16 points as James Madison narrowly beat Wright State 78-76 on Tuesday. Charles Falden capped the scoring with a go-ahead 3-pointer for James Madison with 1:23 left. Vado Morse had 14 points for James Madison (5-1). Takal Molson added 11 points and Terrence Edwards had 10 points. Tanner Holden had 25 points for the Raiders (1-4), who have now lost four games in a row. Grant Basile added 19 points and Tim Finke had 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
